                            <comment id="12942852" author="dejanb" created="Tue, 7 Sep 2010 11:32:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed with svn revision 993322.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;d be great if you could test this new script in your environment&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13193760" author="christianh" created="Thu, 26 Jan 2012 11:30:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix applied does not work on all Solaris installations as /ucr/ucb is not part of the minimal installation bundle.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My suggestion to replace the who am I or whoami is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;`who am i | cut -d &quot; &quot; -f 1`&lt;br/&gt;
From my tests this is platform independend, and for Solaris you can set the application user easy by setting it in activemq.xml from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2907&quot; title=&quot;Solaris 10 SMF manifest&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-2907&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-2907&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Solaris 10 SMF manifest&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
